article.headline: Northwestern St. 103, McNeese State 73
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. (AP) -- Clifton Lee and Kerwin Forges led six players in double figures with 12 points apiece as Northwestern State defeated McNeeese State 103-73 Friday night. The victory secured the Southland Conference regular-season title for the Demons, who will be the top seed in next week's conference tournament. Alfonse Dyer added 11 points for the Demons (19-11, 13-3 Southland). Jermaine Spencer, Tyronn Mitchell and Colby Bargeman each scored 10 points. Bryce May led the Cowboyws (13-14, 8-8) with 14 points. J.T. Williams and Kinley Sellers had 10 points apiece. Mitchell hit a 3-pointer 75 seconds into the second half to put Northwestern ahead 50-31 and the Demons never let the Cowboys closer than 16 points afterward. The lead grew to 30 points, 80-50, with 9:41 to go on a 3-pointer by Forges. It was as large as 34 points in the final two minutes.
